    "Juergen Blickle and his brother Rainer own SEW-Eurodrive, a manufacturer specializing in drive-automation and power-transmission solutions.",
    "The company, acquired by their father, Ernst, in 1945, now employs more than 19,000 people and generates around $3.7 billion in annual revenue.",
    "Its motor, gear and electronic components power conveyors, lifts and other applications in contexts ranging from auto assembly to commercial baking.",
    "In the U.S., it operates a manufacturing plant in Lyman, South Carolina, and has five regional assembly centers and dozens of technical sales offices."
  ],
  "about": [
    "Juergen owns 50% of the company and Rainer, 44.9%. Just over 5% is held by Rainer's charitable foundation.",
    "The brothers shun all publicity; not much is known about them."
  ]
